<div><h3>GAME 245 - Music Composition for Games </h3>  <hr>The course explores advanced game music production concepts and techniques. Topics cover scoring, arranging, and orchestration. Adaptive and non-linear audio concepts are introduced in the context of gameplay, as well as subjects such as looping, branching, and randomization, transition matrices, algorithmic operations, and creating multi-layered stems. Concepts are introduced and explored through applied creative projects. Historical context is given within the development of game music.<br><br><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> GAME 140<br><br><strong>Anticipated Terms Offered:</strong> Spring<br><br></div>		</td>
